<taxonomicName box="[953,1087,1548,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stymphalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stymphalus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
generic complex in having very simple male genitalia. The male pygophore and aedeagus lack processes, and the apophysis of the style lacks rugaeThe genus contains a single species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platymetopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrolineatus">
